-- Market Chatter- Corporate finance press digest
-- 
-- Mon Nov 17, 2014 11:06PM EST
-- None



Nov 18 (Reuters) - The following corporate finance-related stories were reported by media:

* A group led by Canadian property investor Ivanhoe Cambridge has clinched a deal to buy a Manhattan office tower for $2.25 billion from Blackstone Group LP <BX.N>, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing people familiar with the terms of the sale. [ID:nL2N0T801X]  * Merger talks between Hasbro Inc <HAS.O> and DreamWorks Animation SKG Inc <DWA.O> formally ended on Monday morning, when the toy company's board voted to walk away, according to a person with knowledge of the board's actions. [ID:nL2N0T727G]  * Russian Pharmacy Chain 36.6 <APTK.MM> is in talks to acquire the Russian unit of Finnish drug retail and wholesale company Oriola-KD <OKDBV.HE>, a source familiar with the talks said on Monday. [ID:nL6N0T748C]  * Canadian buyout firm Onex Corp <OCX.TO> is leading the bidding for Swiss packaging group SIG Combibloc Group [SIGN.UL], a source familiar with the deal said on Monday. [ID:nL2N0T70EP]  * Malaysian state investor 1 Malaysia Development Bhd (1MDB) took a big step towards a planned $3 billion IPO for its power plant assets, filing a long-awaited application for a flotation that will reduce its huge debt burden, sources said. [ID:nL3N0T738K]  For the deals of the day click on [DEALS/]